tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:848:      "description": "Implement behavior scenarios for methodology boundary, task guard monotonicity, and typed tool-surface capability/transport parity behaviors.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:852:          "description": "Mapped Wave B behaviors have passing positive/falsification scenarios.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:878:      "description": "Implement behavior scenarios for installer/self-host determinism and manual methodology walkthrough coherence.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:980:        "name": "bdd-scenarios",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:991:          "behavior"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:994:        "body": "Behavior proof is expressed as executable `.feature` scenarios (cucumber-rs) tagged with a stable behavior ID (`@BEH-*`). Every in-scope behavior needs both a positive witness (scenario demonstrates the behavior) and a falsification witness (scenario demonstrates the inverse is rejected). Unit and integration tests via `nextest` remain in support of the scenario suite — they do not substitute for scenario ownership of a behavior ID."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1001:        "name": "behavior-traceability",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1016:        "body": "Every testable behavior has a stable `BEH-*` identifier that is referenced from: (1) the spec/plan behavior inventory, (2) the cucumber scenario via a `@BEH-*` tag, (3) mutation survivor triage records, and (4) coverage classification records. Behavior IDs are immutable once published; renames require an abandon+replace event pair in the orchestrator. A behavior claim without a resolvable `BEH-*` link in all four artifacts is treated as incomplete traceability and fails the final gate."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1023:        "name": "coverage-behavior-first",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1033:          "coverage"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1036:        "body": "Coverage is interpreted as a behavior-gap signal, not a vanity percentage. The coverage artifact must classify uncovered paths into two buckets: (1) missing-behavior — code whose absence of coverage corresponds to a behavior without a scenario, which requires adding/extending a `.feature` scenario; and (2) dead/support code — code that is not itself a behavior claim, which requires removal or explicit support-classification. Raw line/branch totals are reported but never gate on their own."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1043:        "name": "mutation-strength",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1053:          "mutation"
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1056:        "body": "Test suites are gated on mutation strength via `cargo-mutants`. Surviving mutants are treated as evidence of weak scenarios: each survivor must be triaged and resolved against a behavior ID (`BEH-*`) — either by tightening an existing scenario, adding a falsification scenario, or explicitly recording the mutant as equivalent with a linked justification. Mutation regressions fail the final gate; the staged `just` recipes surface mutant output in a machine-consumable form for triage."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1077:        "body": "Behavior scenarios may not be skipped, ignored, or conditionally disabled in the cutover suite. `#[ignore]`, `#[cfg(...)]`-gated behavior tests, cucumber `@wip`/`@ignore` tags that bypass CI, and `return Ok(())`-style early exits inside step functions are all prohibited on behavior-owning tests. A failing scenario either gets fixed, its owning behavior gets formally abandoned with an orchestrator event, or the blocker is escalated — it is not hidden. Skip suppression is enforced by the gate tooling, not by convention."
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1091:  "description": "Define stable BEH-* IDs and map Phase 0 Feature 1.1-8.1 behaviors to executable scenario obligations (positive and falsification).",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1095:      "description": "Behavior map covers all in-scope Phase 0 behaviors.",
tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/orchestration/phase0/20260423T001410Z/commands/007-harness_adhere-task.log:1096:      "measurable": "Traceability artifact lists behavior ID -> scenario ownership."
