tanren/specs/rust-testing-hard-cutover-phase0/plan.md:10:The Rust refactor test suite is not compliant with the new behavior-first testing framework standards. Current proof relies on mixed nextest/unit/integration and proof scripts without standards-required BDD-first scenario execution, mutation-strength gating, and behavior-proxy coverage interpretation. We need a hard cutover that resets Rust test assets and rebuilds them systematically against Phase 0 behaviors while preserving per-task demonstrability via just check and final closure via just ci.
